				<a name="management-team"></a>
				<h2 class="bottomSpace">Management Team</h2>
				
				<p>
					Next2Friends is staffed by a global group of talented people from many different 
					disciplines. Its founders are introduced below and full biographies or speaker profiles 
					are available on request.
				</p>
				
				<h3 class="bottomSpace">Roy Shelton, CEO</h3>
				
				<p>
					Roy Shelton has spent the last 22 years building international technology and telecoms 
					businesses including Prime Carrier, Azure Solutions &amp; Cerebrus. Working with government, 
					senior industry and investment communities around the world, Roy has gained a reputation as 
					an early evangelist of the emerging technologies that evolve to lead their field.
				</p>
				
				<p>
					Roy has an MBA from the Open University Business School and is a member of both the 
					Institute of Directors and the Institute of Sales &amp; Marketing Management.
				</p>
				
				<h3 class="bottomSpace">Anthony Nystrom, CTO &amp; Chief Architect</h3>
				
				<p>
					Anthony Nystrom is an accomplished software architect, engineer and versatilist 
					with 12 years proven experience building desktop, enterprise and internet applications. 
					His comprehensive expertise in technical design and development enable Next2Friends to 
					incorporate a multitude of technologies, platforms and programming languages into its 
					platform and roadmap.
				</p>
				
				<p>
					Anthony has a BSc in Computer Science &amp; Mathematics, a BA in Biology &amp; Anthropology 
					and currently has 3 US software patents pending.
				</p>
				
				<h3 class="bottomSpace">Andrew Doyle, COO</h3>
				
				<p>
					Andrew Doyle is a global business executive focused on driving long-lasting financial 
					and operational success for both established global corporations and start-ups for 
					the last 20 years. Andrew’s work in the IT and telecoms industry has generated a 
					wealth of senior industry relationships, and he has worked for companies including 
					Fujitsu, Energis, Racal Telecom and Global Crossing. 
				</p>
				
				<p>
					Andrew has a degree in Business Studies, an Advanced Diploma in Marketing and 
					is a member of the Institute of Directors.
				</p>
				
				<h3 class="bottomSpace">Lawrence Botley, Lead Developer</h3>
				
				<p>
					Lawrence has 12 years experience developing multi-platform ecommerce and 
					telecoms applications for a range of corporations. Lawrence holds a BSc in 
					Artificial Intelligence/Computer Science, an MSc in IT ecommerce and is 
					currently also undertaking a PhD in augmented reality technologies at the 
					University of Sussex.
				</p>
				
				<h3 class="bottomSpace">Gary Nystrom, Senior Developer</h3>
				
				<p>
					Gary has 40 years software development and consulting experience for 
					international businesses including a number of the world’s largest 
					financial institutions, particularly within the areas of high security 
					applications.  Gary holds a BSc in Chemistry &amp; Mathematics, and a BA 
					in Health Sciences.
				</p>
				
				
